<heading id="D08381F6491F0D20FCF3B8ECFB2FF8D2" box="[839,1201,1782,1807]" centered="true" fontSize="10" level="2" pageId="3" pageNumber="44" reason="3">
= 
<taxonomicName id="4C744D19491F0D20FCD9B8EDFB2FF8D2" authority="Gottsche" authorityName="Gottsche" box="[877,1201,1782,1807]" class="Jungermanniopsida" family="Frullaniaceae" genus="Frullania" kingdom="Plantae" order="Porellales" pageId="3" pageNumber="44" phylum="Marchantiophyta" rank="species" species="montagnei">
<emphasis id="B900EA88491F0D20FCD9B8EDFBD7F8D2" bold="true" box="[877,1097,1782,1807]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="44">Frullania montagnei</emphasis>
Gottsche
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCB369A491F0D27FCF3B923FD07FE72" blockId="3.[801,1452,1847,1935]" lastBlockId="4.[136,788,278,431]" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="45" pageId="3" pageNumber="44">
<emphasis id="B900EA88491F0D20FCF3B923FCE1F892" box="[839,895,1848,1871]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="44">Notes</emphasis>
. – 
<taxonomicName id="4C744D19491F0D20FC16B92CFBE7F892" box="[930,1145,1847,1871]" class="Jungermanniopsida" family="Frullaniaceae" genus="Frullania" kingdom="Plantae" order="Porellales" pageId="3" pageNumber="44" phylum="Marchantiophyta" rank="species" species="montagnei">
<emphasis id="B900EA88491F0D20FC16B92CFBE7F892" box="[930,1145,1847,1871]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="44">Frullania montagnei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a rather widespread neotropical species that stands out by rounded leaf tips, undivided hemiphylls, rather small and shallowly bifid underleaves (2–3 × stem width), and gynoecia with a subentire involucre and a 3-keeled perianth (
<bibRefCitation id="EFE54B6B49180D27FEEBBF2CFE60FE92" author="STOTLER, R. E." box="[351,510,311,335]" pageId="4" pageNumber="45" pagination="397 - 555" refId="ref9324" refString="STOTLER, R. E. (1969). The genus Frullania subgenus Frullania in Latin America. Nova Hedwigia 18: 397 - 555." type="journal article" year="1969">STOTLER, 1969</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="4C744D1949180D27FDBABF2CFD62FE92" box="[526,764,311,335]" class="Jungermanniopsida" family="Frullaniaceae" genus="Frullania" kingdom="Plantae" order="Porellales" pageId="4" pageNumber="45" phylum="Marchantiophyta" rank="species" species="gualaquizana">
<emphasis id="B900EA8849180D27FDBABF2CFD62FE92" box="[526,764,311,335]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="45">Frullania gualaquizana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is identical to 
<taxonomicName id="4C744D1949180D27FEB7BF43FE1DFEB2" box="[259,387,344,367]" class="Jungermanniopsida" family="Frullaniaceae" genus="Frullania" kingdom="Plantae" order="Porellales" pageId="4" pageNumber="45" phylum="Marchantiophyta" rank="species" species="montagnei">
<emphasis id="B900EA8849180D27FEB7BF43FE1DFEB2" box="[259,387,344,367]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="45">F. montagnei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and a synonym. The specimen in 
<emphasis id="B900EA8849180D27FD6ABF43FE9AFE52" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="45">Bryo. Levier 6480</emphasis>
is chosen here as the 
<typeStatus id="54CF883849180D27FE5FBF6CFDD5FE52" box="[491,587,375,399]" pageId="4" pageNumber="45">lectotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4C744D1949180D27FDDBBF63FC8CFE52" box="[623,786,375,399]" class="Jungermanniopsida" family="Frullaniaceae" genus="Frullania" kingdom="Plantae" order="Porellales" pageId="4" pageNumber="45" phylum="Marchantiophyta" rank="species" species="gualaquizana">
<emphasis id="B900EA8849180D27FDDBBF63FC8CFE52" box="[623,786,375,399]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="45">F. gualaquizana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as it was illustrated in 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE54B6B49180D27FEC6BF8CFDBFFE72" author="STEPHANI, F." box="[370,545,407,431]" pageId="4" pageNumber="45" refId="ref9306" refString="STEPHANI, F. (1985). Icones Hepaticarum. Microfiche edition. IDC, Zug." type="book" year="1985">STEPHANI (1985</bibRefCitation>
: tab. 4038).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
